  "text": "In this paper, we proposed an algorithm for incremental learning within a meta-learning setup. Incremental learning during meta-training provides a more realistic scenario for real-world few-shot applications where more and more rare classes are seen over time. To the best of our knowledge, we are the first to propose such an experimental setup using existing few-shot classification datasets. We show empirical results on standard benchmark datasets and show that our algorithm is very close to the performance obtained by using Table 3 : Results of classification accuracy on different sets of tiered-ImageNet using our method and meta-training using [CITATION_1] . The evaluation is performed on 2000 episodes and we report the mean and the 95% confidence interval. Table 4 : Results of 5-shot 5-way classification accuracy of our method on different sets of domain-ImageNet using [CITATION_2] as meta-learning algorithm. The evaluation is performed on 2000 episodes and we report the mean and the 95% confidence interval. Figure 4 : Performance of the model on the number of exemplars kept while meta-training was done using base exemplars. Increasing number of exemplars to retain did not yield any positive advantange.",
